Surely the League of Antonican Bards will choose to fight against Mayong.  Surely those aligned with the Ring of Scale would choose to fight against Mayong.<br>
<br>
Gore is mortal, no matter what flaws he may have.  I don't see League of Honor or the League of Shadows bending to his will anytime soon.  Lord Mayong is a god in all but name, and I know of no oaths by which he can be bound, and who alone amongst us is strong enough to stand up to him, let alone his primary agent in Thrads.<br>
<br>
Evil and good have nothing to do with it.  Honor and loyalty have nothing to do it.  Both are evil, both have folk who respect and honor them.  So what.  <br>
<br>
I will be there fighting against Thrads. <br>
<br>
Ayida the Winnower, Harbinger of Destruction, Devotee of Durga <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udamienlogos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Damien Logos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 80<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/23/02 3:02:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm39.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=325.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://razza.org/ephestione/Download/Pictures/Fantasy/WomenandBeasts/images/strahd.jpg width=93 height=146></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmmm.</span><hr size=1> Ayida, you know so little.  This has nothing to do with Mayong.  It has everything to do with another of the servants of the gods being slain.  What happens when they're all gone, and the land consumes you?  You believe so passionately that Mayong wishes to enslave everyone... why has he not then?  Have you not seen Gore already take slaves?  Have you not seen him burn down the foreign quarter of Neriak?  And who was there, to help rebuild it?  Thrads.  Mayong is indeed far more powerful, but his desires are differant that Gore's.  Gore wishes to see the world burn, and be consumed in an inferno of chaos and war.<br>
