<br>
The chants of war echoed off in the distance.  Fire danced upon the lake, howls of foreign tongues filled the air, loud enough to hear, but fading to a whisper when Cook strained to listen to them.<br>
<br>
The force of magic was with him strongly tonight.  He felt the mana surround him, and his eyes glistened at every step he took towards the Arena.<br>
<br>
All those who dare to threaten and insult his allies would share the same fate.<br>
<br>
Surely he would not survive the endevour, as the blades of war always seem to have a way of reaching him.<br>
<br>
But he would drop as many of the misguided fools as he could, including Gore the Mad.<br>
<br>
He would burn them ALL to the ground until he was spent.  And then he would continue fighting until his body lay still.<br>
<br>
Lord Solusek would not let his disciple lay forever slain, Cook mused.  And everyone loves a good bonfire...<br>
